<div class="mediaArea">
    <h2>Upload via the web</h2>
    <ol>
<li>Go to http://unitube.otago.ac.nz</li>
<li>Login by clicking on the login button, top right of screen. This will take you to a page where you will be prompted to enter your usual University of Otago login details. Once you are logged in, you will be taken to the 'My Media' area of UniTube. You will see your username at the top right of the screen.</li>
<li>You will see that you have an option to upload a media file.</li>
<li>Click on 'Choose File' and select the file you want to upload from your own computer system. 'Hidden' is the default setting. For an explanation of the public, hidden and private settings, click on 'Show more' next to the heading 'UniTube security and privacy'.)</li>
<li>Click 'Upload'.</li>
<li>You will see a message saying that your media is being uploaded, with a link to click on in order to see your file. Depending on the file size, this may take some time (a few minutes).</li>
<li>Click on the link to see your file. You will also receive an email notification stating that you have uploaded the file. The link to the file will be included in the email.</li>
<li>You will now be able to see your media file. Underneath it will be the URL (web address) and embed codes for you to copy and share with others.</li>
</ol>
</div>